    "comment": "Rationale: In this study, Huttner et al. isolated synaptic vesicles (SVs) from rat brain to virtual homogeneity (Fig. 6). Using an antibody specific for synapsin 1, a high enrichment of the protein in the purified SV fraction was observed (Figs. 3, 4). The interaction between synapsin and synaptic vesicles was abolished when the ionic strength of the medium was increased, suggesting an electrostatic component in the membrane association (Fig. 9). Also, they showed that phosphorylation of synapsin at the domain involved in the binding to synaptic vesicles decreases the binding between synapsin I and synaptic vesicles (Figs. 11-13).\n\n5/2/2018 Pim\n- Synapsin 1 has a region that binds phospholipids with a preference for negatively charged species. For this reason the 'extrinsic component ...' variant was selected.. Experimental description: Seven rats were killed by cervical dislocation followed by decapitation. The brains were removed from the skull and placed into an ice-cold \"buffered sucrose\" (320 mM sucrose/4 mM HEPES-NaOH buffer, pH 7.3). From this point on, the material was kept at 4°C throughout the preparation.",
